entry.title: [//media] Simplify MailboxVideoFrameConverter texture target calculation
entry.content:
This CL simplifies the logic of MailboxVideoFrameConverter's calculation

of the texture target to use: it needs to use the external target iff

using external sampling and should use GL_TEXTURE_2D otherwise. In this

case, using external sampling is equivalent to "the buffer format passed

in is multiplanar": the current calculation for this use case always

uses BufferPlane::DEFAULT, which signifies external sampling rather

than per-plane sampling when used with multiplanar textures.



As this logic is the platform-specific and service-side equivalent of

the logic that we are rolling out with

ClientSharedImage::GetTextureTarget(), we put this change under the

same killswitch.



In the long term, this change will be able to be ported to use

ClientSharedImage::GetTextureTarget() directly, as this use case will

itself be ported to use ClientSharedImage. There is a fairly lengthy

road to get there though.

entry.title: [//gpu] Remove usage of GetPlatformSpecificTextureTarget()
entry.content:
OzoneImageTexturesHolder invokes GetPlatformSpecificTextureTarget().

Instances of this class are created by the OzoneImageBacking when it

produces GL textures [1]. They can thus be created only on ChromeOS and

Linux (the third Ozone platform is Fuchsia, but Fuchsia does not support

GL at all and thus cannot create GL textures for this class to hold).

For ChromeOS and Linux the platform-specific texture target is

GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL_OES [1]. This CL hardcodes that target as part of

removing all usage of GetPlatformSpecificTextureTarget() outside of

ClientSharedImage.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:gpu/command_buffer/service/shared_image/ozone_image_backing.cc;l=344;drc=e9fe61fd0dc3b731e9ee186f9dde74d986e3592d;bpv=1;bpt=1

[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:gpu/command_buffer/common/gpu_memory_buffer_support.cc;l=184-186?q=GetPlatformSpecificTextur&ss=chromium

entry.title: Remove LacrosSharedComponentsDir flag and switch
entry.content:
This change removes the LacrosSharedComponentsDir feature's flag and

switch, but maintains its behavior.



While storing Lacros components in a shared directory within

/home/chronos did not directly cause issues, the feature's

enabling switch was not consistently propagated to all processes

(beyond the browser process).



This inconsistency could lead to problems with Widevine, which

must establish its hint file's directory in both the browser and a

utility process.



By ensuring Lacros always uses the shared components directory,

this change eliminates the need to propagate the switch across all

processes.

entry.title: Revert "Reland "Reorder precedence of Cookie Access Grants""
entry.content:
This reverts commit d1cd395e3557aa8690b2f5620c2c1742cedc4ce8.



Reason for revert: The test is still failing on some linux/chromeos bots:



https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/linux-bfcache-rel/57652/overview

https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chrome/builders/ci/linux-chromeos-chrome/40308/overview

https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20Tests/142697/overview



Original change's description:

> Reland "Reorder precedence of Cookie Access Grants"

>

> This is a reland of commit 9808ffb946ced743655507f56986b0fe9cea5019

>

> The test is flaky at the level histogram bucket count, reporting 1 count instead of 2 base on cookie write/reads with ExecJs. This reland disables the flaky platforms with a tracking bug to resolve the flakiness.

>

> Original change's description:

> > Reorder precedence of Cookie Access Grants

> >

> > This CL set precedence to allow first priority consideration of our long term solutions, to enhance visibility on their web ecosystem adoption.

> > Similarly, sites controlled mechanisms should be check before Chrome

> > ones, and user controlled mechanisms should come last as in an ideal

> > scenario users shouldn't need to trigger them.

> >

> > The predefined and defaulted controls will always come first.

entry.content:
Previously, code shared by native paint worklet animations composited clip paths and composited bgcolor animations would depend on checking their respective individual feature flags.

entry.title: Fix bisect-builds.py to work with ASan builds.
entry.content:
- Add a `/` to the prefix when enumerating ASan build: this speeds up

enumeration of linux-release builds by avoiding useless enumeration of

linux-release-chromeos and linux-release-v8-arm builds.

- Use the correct archive name for Linux: after r398598, the ASan base

path on Linux matches other platforms. No attempt is made to handle

the legacy archive name, as r398598 is nearly 8 years old at this

point.

- Handle handle zip archives when a entry's file name has no directory

component. os.path.dirname('only_filename') returns an empty string,

and trying to make a directory with no name fails.

- Unzip ASan archive into a subdirectory rather than directly into the

temp directory, as that is what the rest of the script expects.

- Remove the custom result evaluator for ASan since ASan builds may

encounter safety violations unrelated to the bug being evaluated

Instead, have the script print out any detected ASan errors to stdout

and allow the user to make a manual determination.
